main_body:
The Belgian Government is hereby authorized to grant aid totalling Bfr 2 587 970 000 to the Belgian coal industry for the 1991 calendar year. The total amount shall be made up of the following aid:
1. aid to cover operating losses not exceeding Bfr 2 257 570 000;
2. aid to finance social benefit schemes in the coal industry not exceeding Bfr 292 700 000;
3. aid to cover expenses relating to the system of supplementary holiday for underground workers, not exceeding Bfr 37 700 000.
